1
00:00:01,010 --> 00:00:02,010
(Episode 83)

2
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,480
It's true that...

3
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:05,540
I was the one
who was prescribed sleeping medication.

4
00:00:06,850 --> 00:00:08,910
Even though I saw my mother suffering
from insomnia,

5
00:00:09,380 --> 00:00:10,920
I shouldn't have done that.

6
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:16,520
So please, blame me. But as for my mother,

7
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,160
please find it in your hearts
to forgive her.

8
00:00:19,990 --> 00:00:22,160
Are you saying CEO Chae Hwa Young...

9
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,830
had sleeping medication
prescribed in your name...

10
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:26,770
and then took the injections herself?

11
00:00:32,140 --> 00:00:33,640
CEO Chae, is that true?

12
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,370
- Is your daughter being truthful?
- Any comment?

13
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:37,580
- CEO, is it really true?
- We need a comment!

14
00:00:41,910 --> 00:00:43,880
Chae Hwa Young. An eye for an eye.

15
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:47,690
I'm just paying you back
for the despicable trick you pulled.

16
00:00:54,690 --> 00:00:57,130
You wicked witch!

17
00:00:57,130 --> 00:00:59,760
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

18
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:02,470
You nasty, insolent brat!

19
00:01:02,830 --> 00:01:05,140
How dare you pull such a sly stunt
in front of my Jun Ho!

20
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:13,880
What's going on, CEO Chae?

21
00:01:14,780 --> 00:01:17,420
Stop that interview
Seo Rin is giving right now.

22
00:01:17,750 --> 00:01:21,620
Don't let it be published as an article,
and above all, keep it off social media.

23
00:01:21,690 --> 00:01:22,690
Stop it now!

24
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:24,290
Yes, ma'am.

25
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:36,100
You don't believe me either?

26
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:41,070
That brat, Ma Seo Rin, got the shots
for her insomnia, and she took them.

27
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:42,140
That's odd.

28
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,980
You two are mother and daughter.
Why do you act like you're mortal enemies?

29
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:47,150
Because she's trying to pin it all on me,
that's why!

30
00:01:47,610 --> 00:01:48,680
That sly little witch.

31
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,120
Enough.

32
00:01:52,650 --> 00:01:54,220
Have you set a date
for our families to meet?

33
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:56,090
Do you really love Oh Jang...

34
00:01:57,220 --> 00:02:00,360
- Are you in love with Seo Rin?
- How many times must I say it? I am.

35
00:02:01,490 --> 00:02:03,190
- And...
- And?

36
00:02:04,030 --> 00:02:06,030
I owe a debt to my parents now...

37
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,730
for saving my life and adopting me
after I was disowned for having leukemia,

38
00:02:10,540 --> 00:02:12,740
I have to make them proud.

39
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,640
No. I will make them proud.

40
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,240
This is absurd. A sense of obligation?

41
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:22,710
Fine, of course you do. They raised you.

42
00:02:23,980 --> 00:02:26,780
But for you to side with me,
your mother, because of them?

43
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:28,650
It's just so disheartening.

44
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,220
It's just basic human decency.

45
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:41,670
Do you think I wanted to abandon you?

46
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:37,720
Right. So Seo Rin solved this problem
all by herself?

47
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,720
I knew she had it in her.

48
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:44,630
By the way, Secretary Kim.

49
00:03:45,530 --> 00:03:50,570
That business with Seo Rin's medication
that we paid to bury.

50
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:54,070
Who had the nerve to dig it up again?

51
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:57,080
Darn that brat! Darn her!

52
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:58,710
Please, calm down.

53
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:01,210
At this rate, I'm worried
you'll make yourself sick, CEO Chae.

54
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:04,680
You haven't been
out of the detention center for very long.

55
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:05,750
Exactly.

56
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:10,090
The minute I get out, that Oh Jang Mi brat
tries to screw me over. I'm furious!

57
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:12,860
I need to get rid of that little witch,
and fast.

58
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,260
I'm so upset, I'm going to lose my mind.

59
00:04:16,330 --> 00:04:19,730
And my own daughter, Seo Rin, is in a coma
because she was hurt instead.

60
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:22,730
I'm worried about
what happened to Seo Rin too.

61
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:26,300
She has to wake up safe and sound...

62
00:04:27,610 --> 00:04:30,240
so she can help me achieve my dream.

63
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:35,980
It's Lawyer Han Young Ja.

64
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:39,080
I bet she's calling about
Jun Ho's wedding.

65
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:47,290
- Hello, this is Chae Hwa Young.
- CEO Chae, is now a good time to talk?

66
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:52,730
Yes. The reason I'm calling
is about our Jun Ho.

67
00:04:53,230 --> 00:04:56,530
He says he's determined
to marry Director Ma,

68
00:04:57,200 --> 00:05:00,570
and he's asked me to help
move things along.

69
00:05:01,010 --> 00:05:03,940
- I see.
- I know you must be very busy.

70
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:08,280
I was hoping we could meet to discuss
the children's wedding when you're free.

71
00:05:08,510 --> 00:05:13,120
- When would be a good time for you?
- Anytime is fine with me.

72
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:17,060
In that case, how about
this weekend evening?

73
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:22,560
I'm not a great cook, but our housekeeper
makes some delicious dishes.

74
00:05:23,230 --> 00:05:26,130
Why don't we have dinner at our place
and discuss it then?

75
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,370
Yes, that sounds lovely.

76
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,770
Baek Ho, I should get going now.

77
00:05:33,170 --> 00:05:34,570
- Okay.
- Yes.

78
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:37,610
Wait, hold on!
You're just going to leave like that?

79
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:40,510
- Aren't you forgetting something?
- I am?

80
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,080
What did I forget?

81
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:46,080
You have to give me my stamp right here.
How could you forget something so crucial?

82
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:54,960
Not this again. You're impossible.

83
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:58,330
- Let's just keep this professional.
- But I like it this way. See?

84
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,070
That's it for today.

85
00:06:01,470 --> 00:06:03,770
- See you tomorrow.
- All right, get home safe.

86
00:06:19,350 --> 00:06:21,550
- What is it?
- I need to talk to you.

87
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,230
If you have something to say, spit it out.

88
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:32,160
Baek Ho, you've known this whole time...

89
00:06:32,330 --> 00:06:35,400
that Director Ma
and Oh Jang Mi were twins.

90
00:06:35,570 --> 00:06:36,770
Why are you keeping it a secret
from everyone?

91
00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:40,510
- I'm not hiding anything.
- Then have you told the Chairman...

92
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:42,170
and Director Ma about Oh Jang Mi?

93
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:46,280
See? You are hiding something.

94
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,550
What are you getting at?

95
00:06:47,810 --> 00:06:48,910
My mother and I...

96
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:52,750
get that Director Ma
and Oh Jang Mi are twins.

97
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:55,250
- And?
- But why?

98
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:59,320
I don't understand how
CEO Chae could give birth to twins...

99
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:00,790
but only raise one of them.

100
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:04,630
And why would Oh Jang Mi
report CEO Chae, her own mother,

101
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:07,230
as the suspect in her father's murder?

102
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:08,730
You know, don't you, Baek Ho?

103
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,370
Please, just tell me what you know.

104
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,970
And why should I tell you anything,
Team Leader Jin?

105
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,170
You know where Oh Jang Mi is.

106
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:20,480
Let Director Ma and Oh Jang Mi meet
so we can get to the bottom of this.

107
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:30,590
Chae Hwa Young!

108
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,390
- What do you think you're doing?
- You insolent little brat.

109
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:35,760
You're the one who started this.

110
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:39,300
On the surface, you and I are
mother and daughter.

111
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:42,830
So why would a mother
turn in her own daughter like that?

112
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,370
Who do you think is the reason
Seo Rin's in pain?

113
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,940
With a mother like you,
is it any wonder Seo Rin has insomnia?

114
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:51,040
I was utterly humiliated because of you.

115
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,210
Oh Jang Mi,
does that make you feel better?

116
00:07:53,410 --> 00:07:55,850
You're throwing a fit over
a little bit of humiliation?

117
00:07:56,810 --> 00:08:00,550
You killed my father
and drove Seo Rin to this.

118
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:03,290
And that's not all.
You also murdered Ssangkal.

119
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:06,320
A murderer talking about being humiliated?
Don't make me laugh.

120
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,760
- You're being ridiculous.
- Why you...

121
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:15,670
My goodness. What is going on?

122
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:17,840
What the heck do you think you're doing?

123
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:21,570
This is my grandfather's house,
so it's my house and the Ma family home.

124
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:23,810
And you have the nerve to slap me in here?

125
00:08:24,380 --> 00:08:28,650
- What right do you have? Know your place.
- You little witch, are you done talking?

126
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:30,950
Without Grandfather,
I'm the rightful heir to the Ma family.

127
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:32,250
This is all mine.

128
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:35,720
- So how dare you lay a hand on me?
- What gives you the right to push me?

129
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:38,320
I've never met such a vile,
despicable brat!

130
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:41,490
Hey, stop it, both of you!
Goodness, calm down!

131
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:42,830
- Get out of my way.
- Oh! Goodness!

132
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,430
Oh, dear. My goodness.

133
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:47,370
Real nice.

134
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,570
Treating Grandfather's wife
with such disrespect.

135
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:52,040
Seo Rin.

136
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:54,610
You have no manners.
You don't respect your elders, do you?

137
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:57,070
You don't even know your own place.
Who are you to lecture anyone?

138
00:08:57,170 --> 00:08:59,810
What's all this commotion?

139
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,910
Grandfather! Mom...

140
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:04,980
Mom hit me.

141
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,250
Seo Rin!

142
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,020
CEO Chae!

143
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,560
I want a word with you. Now!

144
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:18,830
You...

145
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:20,730
Have you lost your mind?

146
00:09:21,930 --> 00:09:24,600
After everything I did to get you
out of that awful mess,

147
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,670
you dare lay a hand on Seo Rin?

148
00:09:27,570 --> 00:09:28,570
Father.

149
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:32,940
I'm truly grateful that you pulled strings
with your connections for me.

150
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,150
I was already preparing something
to show my gratitude...

151
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:38,980
But why would you take it out
on poor Seo Rin and slap her?

152
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:43,320
Are you doing this because
Seo Rin threw you under the bus...

153
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:44,820
over that injection incident?

154
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:48,290
She was just trying to save
her own skin by blaming you.

155
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:51,500
You're her mother.
You couldn't even take the fall for her?

156
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,260
How can you even call yourself her mother?

157
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,570
Father.

158
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:58,840
Seo Rin lied at the press conference
without even talking to me,

159
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,470
so of course I was upset.

160
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:03,270
I barely just got out
of the detention center,

161
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:06,640
- and I can barely face the employees.
- What about you?

162
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:10,820
Did you even look into why that drug story
came out in the first place?

163
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:16,190
That's a case
we already buried once before,

164
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:18,620
so why is it suddenly resurfacing?

165
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:22,960
Who dared to leak this to the press
and stir up all this trouble?

166
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,830
If you want to protect your own daughter,

167
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,230
shouldn't you be investigating that first?

168
00:10:28,830 --> 00:10:31,970
Is this old geezer on my case
because he knows I'm the leaker?

169
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:35,170
And like I told you before,
I'm not letting this slide.

170
00:10:35,810 --> 00:10:37,010
Your one percent stake.

171
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,780
Sign it over to Seo Rin.

172
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:43,410
- I can't do that, Father.
- Did you forget the promise you made me?

173
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:47,550
Should I make you pay for all the damages
our company suffered...

174
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,250
while you were in jail?

175
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,240
This is insane! I'm so sick of this.

176
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:07,470
So sick of it!

177
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,610
I'm so sick and tired of this!

178
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,080
You monster, Chae Hwa Young.

179
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:18,120
Don't you dare whine about your suffering.
You haven't seen anything yet.

180
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,220
Compared to the pain my family suffered...

181
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,750
and what Seo Rin and I have endured,

182
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:24,990
what you're feeling now
is just a drop in the bucket.

183
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:37,800
There you are.

184
00:11:41,610 --> 00:11:44,580
Did you ask Lawyer Kang
where Oh Jang Mi is?

185
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:48,880
If he were the type to talk,
he would've given her up already.

186
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:52,280
So he's keeping his mouth shut, then?

187
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:57,190
- Yes.
- Gosh, when are we going to solve this?

188
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:02,290
By the way, Hong Ju,
something's off with Seo Rin and CEO Chae.

189
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:03,830
What do you mean?

190
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,730
They're a mother and daughter,
but they act like mortal enemies.

191
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,930
- Really?
- Yes.

192
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,000
I wonder why.

193
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:13,540
You think Seo Rin found out
that her mom abandoned Oh Jang Mi?

194
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,160
Professor Kang.

195
00:12:43,570 --> 00:12:46,140
Did you come here knowing I'd be here?

196
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,400
No.

197
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:50,840
I just came for a drink
because I was upset about something,

198
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,140
and you just happened to be here.

199
00:13:22,570 --> 00:13:23,910
You and I...

200
00:13:25,410 --> 00:13:27,910
I guess we're fated
to keep running into each other.

201
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:32,420
Even when we try not to, we keep running
into each other like this.

202
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:39,020
Or maybe you came here on purpose,
not by chance.

203
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:42,390
I don't trust you anymore, CEO Chae.

204
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:49,270
What's this? Why are you crying?

205
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:52,870
Is this your new strategy?
Trying to win me over with tears?

206
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:56,340
No. I'm not appealing for anything.

207
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:57,780
It's not like that at all.

208
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:00,950
Then why are you crying?

209
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,880
I'm sorry.

210
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,980
I can't help it.
The tears just keep coming.

211
00:14:09,220 --> 00:14:11,920
It feels like the one person I believed
was always on my side...

212
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:15,930
is walking away, and I'm just watching
his back disappear,

213
00:14:17,130 --> 00:14:20,460
leaving me all alone
in a vast, empty field.

214
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:24,130
My heart aches,

215
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,540
and I feel so lonely and desolate.

216
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,680
Professor Kang.

217
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:35,650
Do you hate me that much?

218
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:38,550
I haven't done anything wrong to you.

219
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:41,390
- I don't want to hear it. Just stop.
- No.

220
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,150
I'm going to say everything now.

221
00:14:43,490 --> 00:14:46,490
I can't stay silent
when this is so unfair.

222
00:14:48,490 --> 00:14:52,160
You're misunderstanding me.
I'm the one being wronged here.

223
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,230
What exactly do you think I did wrong?

224
00:14:56,970 --> 00:15:01,110
Why did the person
who took the fall for you die in prison?

225
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:06,380
You ordered the hit, didn't you?

226
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:09,750
In the end, you murdered Oh Bok Gil,

227
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:12,180
and then you framed me for it.

228
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:16,690
Do I really have to spell it out for you?

229
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,160
Answer me!

230
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:21,960
This is so absurd.
I'm at a loss for words.

231
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,260
Nam Bong, so this whole time,

232
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:26,660
you’ve been dating me
thinking I was that kind of woman?

233
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:28,800
That's insane.

234
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:32,240
How could you even think
something so horrible?

235
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:36,210
- So you're saying you didn't do it?
- Of course not! Absolutely not.

236
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:40,510
My goodness! Me?
How could I ever do something like that?

237
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:42,910
How could I hire someone
to murder another person?

238
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:45,150
And someone in jail, no less?
How could I have done that?

239
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,420
Does that even make any sense?

240
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:58,260
After I lost Seo Rin's father,

241
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:01,330
I didn't date anyone for 30 years.

242
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,770
I just lived under Chairman Ma's wing,

243
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,040
shuttling between the hotel and home,

244
00:16:08,570 --> 00:16:10,740
as a woman who lived only for her work.

245
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:15,880
But then, for the very first time,
when I met you, Nam Bong,

246
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:18,850
my heart fluttered with excitement.

247
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:22,050
For the first time,
I felt like a woman again.

248
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,690
I wondered why I hadn't met you sooner.

249
00:16:26,620 --> 00:16:30,290
I even imagined starting
a family with you,

250
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,700
and for the first time,
I found happiness outside of work.

251
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:36,870
I was happy just being myself,
Chae Hwa Young, not CEO Chae.

252
00:16:37,970 --> 00:16:40,000
All because I was in love with you.

253
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:42,770
After feeling all of that,

254
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:46,540
how could I turn around and frame you?

255
00:16:47,710 --> 00:16:49,850
Isn't that a horrifying thing
to even imagine?

256
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:54,050
For me to kill someone,
when I feel this way about you?

257
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:55,850
How is that even possible?

258
00:16:57,990 --> 00:16:59,020
I don't know anymore.

259
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,030
One person tells me one thing,

260
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:04,960
and it sounds true.

261
00:17:08,230 --> 00:17:09,900
Then you tell me your side, Hwa Young,

262
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,340
and I feel like I've had it all wrong.

263
00:17:17,710 --> 00:17:20,140
Nam Bong, I really didn't do it.

264
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,110
I'm being completely wronged.

265
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:25,320
Most of all,

266
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:28,820
I can't bear the thought
of you misunderstanding me.

267
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:32,660
It really wasn't me. Please believe me.

268
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:38,060
They let me go because I'm innocent.

269
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:42,370
Is our country's justice system
that incompetent? Of course not.

270
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:45,300
I'm truly innocent.

271
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,910
If I misunderstood you...

272
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:53,510
I'm sorry, Hwa Young.

273
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:04,350
Nam Bong.

274
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:07,020
You'll believe me, won't you?

275
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:09,290
- Right?
- Don't worry.

276
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:13,060
Nam Bong, I love you.

277
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,740
Please, stop whining.
It's hard for me, too.

278
00:18:22,910 --> 00:18:26,240
Jang Mi, I'm putting Mom on.
Try to talk some sense into her.

279
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:30,110
- What's going on?
- Mom keeps whining about seeing Tok Hee.

280
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:33,220
I think her Chae Hwa Young's men
are posted outside watching us,

281
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,050
so we can't risk going to visit Seo Rin.

282
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:38,360
Okay. Put Mom on, Tae Pyung.

283
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:41,160
- Mom.
- Jang Mi.

284
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:46,600
I'm going to see Tok Hee.
Suk Hee wants to play with Tok Hee.

285
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:50,800
- I miss Tok Hee.
- You miss Tok Hee?

286
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:55,240
Tok Hee is sick.
Suk Hee has to sing her a lullaby.

287
00:18:55,540 --> 00:18:58,340
Let's just get through tonight
and go tomorrow, okay?

288
00:18:58,910 --> 00:19:01,180
So just hang in there a little longer.

289
00:19:01,580 --> 00:19:02,650
"Hang in there a little longer?"

290
00:19:03,780 --> 00:19:04,820
Who were you talking to?

291
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:08,290
It's none of your business.

292
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:16,130
"Let's just get through tonight
and go tomorrow."

293
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:19,900
"So just hang in there
for a little longer." What?

294
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:22,300
Who was she talking to?

295
00:19:23,470 --> 00:19:24,470
Jang Mi?

296
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:27,670
Jang Mi's gone. She hung up.

297
00:19:28,010 --> 00:19:31,010
- Grandma, let me see.
- Okay.

298
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:33,280
She really did hang up.

299
00:19:34,010 --> 00:19:35,450
She must've been in a bad spot to talk.

300
00:19:36,650 --> 00:19:39,680
- Mom, you heard what Jang Mi said, right?
- Yes.

301
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:41,150
But still...

302
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,520
I'm worried about Tok Hee.

303
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:48,030
Grandma, take this bunny plush instead,
and you can rock it to sleep.

304
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:52,700
Ma'am.

305
00:19:53,430 --> 00:19:55,430
- It's Baek Ho! You're here.
- I am.

306
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:56,670
You're so sweet, Baek Ho.

307
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,470
I brought your favorite ice cream,

308
00:20:00,170 --> 00:20:03,570
- and Bo Ra's favorite snacks.
- Thank you.

309
00:20:04,010 --> 00:20:06,610
- Bo Ra, let's go eat these.
- Okay.

310
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:08,310
Hey, little bunny.

311
00:20:08,610 --> 00:20:09,610
Let's go.

312
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:16,020
You must be busy.
You didn't have to stop by.

313
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:18,320
I was afraid I'd forget your face.

314
00:20:21,990 --> 00:20:23,030
Hey, Baek Ho.

315
00:20:23,390 --> 00:20:26,360
But seriously,
is Jang Mi really marrying Jun Ho?

316
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,870
- So what's the deal?
- That's not going to happen.

317
00:20:30,130 --> 00:20:31,640
He can't exactly marry himself, can he?

318
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:35,770
Jang Mi is never going to marry
my brother, so don't you worry.

319
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,410
You're the one who should be worried, man.

320
00:20:38,310 --> 00:20:41,780
You better step it up so Jun Ho
doesn't steal her from you, you hear?

321
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:55,930
Jang Mi, are you asleep?

322
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:58,100
No, not yet.

323
00:20:58,630 --> 00:21:01,370
I don't think I'll be able to sleep
until I hear it from you.

324
00:21:02,670 --> 00:21:04,700
- Hear what?
- That you love me.

325
00:21:05,570 --> 00:21:06,600
Do you love me?

326
00:21:06,970 --> 00:21:11,680
- I'm asking, do you love me?
- For goodness' sake. No, I don't.

327
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:15,250
- There. Happy? I'm hanging up.
- Hey, that's not fair.

328
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:18,680
That's what you get for asking
such a cliche question.

329
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:21,220
I'm dying to know,
and you call it a cliche?

330
00:21:22,650 --> 00:21:24,350
What's there to be so worked up about?

331
00:21:26,860 --> 00:21:30,360
You can't get a confession for free.
Show me you mean it.

332
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:31,860
Then I'll tell you I love you.

333
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:35,170
Fine, I'll sing you a song.

334
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:38,000
Get all cozy in bed,
ready to sleep, and listen.

335
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:39,700
I promise it'll help you
drift right off to sleep.

336
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:45,540
I'm getting ready.
Okay, commence operation.

337
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:46,840
Begin.

338
00:21:49,110 --> 00:21:54,650
<i>If you were to ask me what love is</i>

339
00:21:55,790 --> 00:21:58,790
<i>It's more than the initial butterflies</i>

340
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:03,860
<i>It's cherishing the comfort of familiarity</i>

341
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:07,000
<i>Even when things don't go your way</i>

342
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:10,170
<i>It's never giving up</i>

343
00:22:49,570 --> 00:22:52,980
Jang Mi. You were right
about the hotel supply company.

344
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:54,880
For years, they've just been
faking the bidding process.

345
00:22:55,180 --> 00:22:57,950
And it turns out most of the people
involved are connected to CEO Chae.

346
00:22:58,220 --> 00:23:02,190
I bet they're lowballing the prices to
ridiculous levels to build a slush fund.

347
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:05,920
She probably used that fund for bribes
in politics and business to pull strings.

348
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:07,220
I'll have to look into it.

349
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:12,130
By the way, you know Grandfather took
one percent of Chae Hwa Young's shares...

350
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,560
and gave them to me, right?

351
00:23:13,830 --> 00:23:17,600
Of course. I just met with CEO Chae
and handled the paperwork myself.

352
00:23:18,270 --> 00:23:21,170
CEO Chae is probably about to
blow a gasket right about now.

353
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:22,740
Be careful.

354
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:29,550
My patience has its limits.
That piece of trash.

355
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:31,480
I can't let her get away with this.

356
00:23:31,850 --> 00:23:32,920
What are you going to do?

357
00:23:32,980 --> 00:23:36,920
I'll have to teach her what happens
when you mess with Chae Hwa Young.

358
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:42,130
I can't stand watching her strut around
as if she's Ma Seo Rin.

359
00:23:52,370 --> 00:23:53,740
Is this the new uniform?

360
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,010
Yes, that's right.

361
00:23:55,070 --> 00:23:57,370
(4. Main Design Option Three)

362
00:23:57,470 --> 00:23:58,680
(5. Designs by Job Position)

363
00:23:58,740 --> 00:24:00,140
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

364
00:24:00,210 --> 00:24:01,240
Not bad.

365
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:04,580
Did you say the concierge uniforms
arrived today?

366
00:24:04,750 --> 00:24:07,620
Yes, I was told they'll be ready
for inspection in 30 minutes.

367
00:24:07,950 --> 00:24:09,150
Would you like to go yourself?

368
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:12,360
No.

369
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:21,060
This right here...

370
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,300
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

371
00:24:29,310 --> 00:24:31,580
Oh Jang Mi, that insolent little brat.

372
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:35,750
Then again, what can you expect
when her mother's a half-wit?

373
00:24:36,210 --> 00:24:38,780
What brings you here, CEO Chae?

374
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:43,390
I heard the resort's concierge uniforms
arrived today.

375
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:46,660
I was hoping Director Ma could
go inspect them in person.

376
00:24:47,690 --> 00:24:48,690
Director Ma.

377
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:51,630
- Me?
- Of course. Who else would go but you?

378
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:54,500
We agreed that the Dream Project
would handle the Dream Resort...

379
00:24:54,830 --> 00:24:56,970
from start to finish, didn't we?

380
00:24:58,340 --> 00:25:00,100
Fine, I'll do it.

381
00:25:00,970 --> 00:25:04,910
Sure. I'll go see just what a mess
the design you picked is.

382
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:08,810
Keep up the good work, everyone.

383
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:21,790
Manager Lee,
you have our people ready, right?

384
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:23,330
Yes.

385
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:25,360
Jang Mi is on her way there now.

386
00:25:25,930 --> 00:25:27,730
Make sure there are no mistakes this time.

387
00:25:29,030 --> 00:25:33,400
Show that arrogant witch exactly
what happens when she crosses me.

388
00:25:34,070 --> 00:25:35,140
Yes, I understand.

389
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:45,950
Jang Mi. You were right
about the hotel supply company.

390
00:25:45,950 --> 00:25:48,050
For years, they've just been
faking the bidding process.

391
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:49,420
Chae Hwa Young.

392
00:25:49,750 --> 00:25:53,220
I will find out how you're
building your slush fund,

393
00:25:53,290 --> 00:25:55,630
and I'll make you pay big time.
Just you wait.

394
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:00,530
You'll catch a cold.

395
00:26:04,230 --> 00:26:06,540
- What's this for?
- You've never been in the laundry room?

396
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:09,870
The laundry room is way more
dangerous than the kitchen.

397
00:26:10,210 --> 00:26:11,810
Plus, the detergents are incredibly harsh.

398
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:16,380
Just folding the restaurant tablecloths
for a day will make your hands raw.

399
00:26:16,650 --> 00:26:19,380
I thought you were only a good chef,

400
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,850
but you know your way around
the laundry room too?

401
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:28,460
Don't go thinking I'm falling for you
just because of that. Dream on.

402
00:26:28,660 --> 00:26:31,630
The fact that you'd even say that
means I'm on your mind.

403
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:33,360
Am I wrong?

404
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:35,970
My gosh...

405
00:26:38,370 --> 00:26:39,370
Of course not!

406
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:54,990
(Caution: High-temperature Steam)

407
00:26:56,390 --> 00:26:57,820
Alright, just stick close to me.

408
00:26:58,360 --> 00:27:00,460
Please. I'm fine.

409
00:27:01,790 --> 00:27:04,190
Director Ma. This way, please.

410
00:27:04,530 --> 00:27:06,230
Right, okay.

411
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:37,530
(Caution: High-temperature Steam)

412
00:27:41,530 --> 00:27:42,570
Darn it!

413
00:27:53,710 --> 00:27:54,710
Jun Ho!

414
00:27:55,380 --> 00:27:57,780
Jun Ho! Are you okay?

415
00:27:58,050 --> 00:28:00,580
Here! Over here! Hurry!

416
00:28:00,850 --> 00:28:03,490
Someone call an ambulance! Hurry!

417
00:28:04,390 --> 00:28:06,920
- Seo Rin...
- What?

418
00:28:07,690 --> 00:28:10,930
Oh no. Jun Ho! What do I do?

419
00:28:11,130 --> 00:28:15,430
Jun Ho!

420
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:17,470
Somebody call an ambulance!

421
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,000
Hurry!

422
00:28:42,630 --> 00:28:44,230
(The First Man)

423
00:28:44,290 --> 00:28:48,400
So, you've finally grasped the situation.
I'll give you one week. Exactly one week.

424
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:51,200
Find Oh Jang Mi by then. Got it?

425
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:53,770
That's right.
I'm going to be honest with my feelings.

426
00:28:54,070 --> 00:28:55,570
I don't want to live like this anymore.

427
00:28:55,870 --> 00:28:57,410
Oh my, what's this?

428
00:28:57,910 --> 00:29:01,480
Chae Hwa Young!
So Jun Ho is your most precious person.

429
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:04,210
Losing him
or having him stolen from you would be...

430
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:06,180
the most painful revenge, wouldn't it?

431
00:29:07,650 --> 00:29:09,650
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
